# Project overview
- This repo is a PlatformIO-based template for Arduino, ESP32, and RP2040 boards.
- Primary workflow: VS Code + PlatformIO.
- arduino-cli is optional and used only for .ino sketch folders like ./blink and ./oled_hello.

# Entry points
- PlatformIO firmware entry point: src/main.cpp
- PlatformIO environments are defined in platformio.ini:
  - [env:uno] for Arduino Uno
  - [env:esp32dev] for ESP32 dev boards
  - [env:pico] for RP2040 / Raspberry Pi Pico
- Arduino CLI sketches:
  - ./blink (blink/blink.ino)
  - ./oled_hello (oled_hello/oled_hello.ino)

# Commands the assistant should prefer
- Build & upload to Uno via PlatformIO:
  - pio run -t upload -e uno
- Build & upload to ESP32:
  - pio run -t upload -e esp32dev
- Build & upload to Pico:
  - pio run -t upload -e pico
- Upload blink via arduino-cli:
  - arduino-cli compile --fqbn arduino:avr:uno ./blink
  - arduino-cli upload -p /dev/cu.usbserial-DN050KN9 --fqbn arduino:avr:uno ./blink

# Coding preferences
- Use src/main.cpp as the main firmware for PlatformIO; do not create random new entry files.
- When adding new examples:
  - Put PlatformIO versions under src/ (or clearly named .cpp files).
  - Put Arduino-IDE/CLI versions in separate .ino folders.
- Keep README.md as the main documentation; update it instead of adding extra doc files.
- Do not remove arduino-cli.ini; keep it as optional CLI support.

